# DATE: 2026-02-13
# AUTHOR: Keimpe de Jong
USAGE:
- Instantiate or mix into an AccessibilityAgent implementation.
- Call analyze_file(file_path: str) to scan a file on disk and receive an AccessibilityReport.
- Call analyze_content(content: str, file_type: str = "html") to scan an in-memory string."- Toggle checks with enable_rule(wcag_criterion: str) and disable_rule(wcag_criterion: str).

WHAT IT DOES:
Provides a compact, file- and content-oriented entry point for accessibility analysis in AccessibilityAgent instances. It clears and collects issues, dispatches to file-type specific analyzers (_analyze_html, _analyze_python_ui, _analyze_javascript_ui), and produces an AccessibilityReport via _generate_report. Also exposes simple rule toggles by WCAG criterion keys stored in self.rules.

WHAT IT SHOULD DO BETTER:
- Validate inputs and surface clear errors for missing analyzers or unsupported file types instead of returning an empty report silently.
- Normalize and document expected shape of self.issues, self.rules, and the AccessibilityReport to avoid coupling surprises.
- Add logging, configurable rule-sets, asynchronous analysis for large files, and unit-tested adapters for each UI language analyzer to improve robustness and testability.

